==Japanese==
=== Etymology ===
{{ja-kanjitab-top}}
! [[水]] || [[曜]] || [[日]]
{{ja-kanjitab-bottom}}
From Latin ''[[dies Mercurii]]'' ("day of Mercury") through Indian astrology in the fifth century as Sanskrit ''[[saumyavāra]]'' (''saumya'', "of the planet Mercury") into Buddhist astrology in the 8th century as 水曜日: [[水]] (すい, ''sui'', "water", the Buddhist element associated with the planet Mercury) + [[曜日]] (ようび, ''yōbi'', "day of the week").

===Noun===
{{janoun|すいようび|suiyōbi}}
